Text: Thanks for tuning in today and please join us again for tomorrow's rematch!
Le Roux down the middle to finish the match. France struggled in the first two sets today, but they walk away with a 3-1 win.
Rouzier with an ace. 16-10 for France at second TTO.
Le Goff stopped in the middle. 9-6 for France.
Team Korea look a bit deflated at the start of the fourth set. Shin attack long to give France a 4-1 lead. Time-out called by Korea.
France win the third set relatively easy to take a 2-1 lead in the match!
France fans hope their team won't squander the lead again. It's 21-16.
France look strong now as they quickly build a good lead. 10-5.
Rouzier finally manages to close out the set with a block-out! 25-23 and both teams are level again.
A Seo ace followed by an error from Rouzier. 24-23.
Korea are refusing to give up! They stop Tillie to make it 24-21 for France.
Rouzier is dominating the net right now! He extends France's lead to 22-15.
France manage to get the lead they were looking for. A spike and an ace from Rouzier give them a 16-11 lead at second TTO.
The game is still close in the 2nd set as France lead 8-6 at second TTO.
France are furious as the referee decides that a Song spike touched the block. Another quick point for Korea and it is the home team that clinch the first set 30-28!
Songs puts his serve in the net to give France another set point. 28-27.
Tillie block-out. 27-26 for France.
France earn their first set point with a good block, but Rouzier is stopped on the next play. 25-all.
A solid Koga spike hands the home team their first set point. 24-23.
Error no. 12 for France in the opening set as Rouzier attacks wide. 23-22 for Korea.
What an exciting finish to the set! Ngapeth spikes the ball long to make it 22-all.
Another France error gives the home team their first lead of the day. TO for France at 20-19.
A soft touch over the block by Chijiki. 19-all.
France are quick to react, though. Ngapeth with a block-out and Korea call a TO at 19-16 for France.
Korea don't give up. A Song ace brings them close at 17-16 for France.
Rouzier with a booming ace. 16-13 for France at second TTO.
Ace from Nagano levels things up at 11-all.
France start strong as they lead 8-5 at first TTO.
Opening show before the match
45 mins to go!!!
